Enable Agents To Test Their Workstations with Voice Status Utility

To help agents check whether their workspace is ready for Service Cloud Voice, add the Voice Status utility to console apps or Voice extensions. When agents click Run Test from the Voice Status utility, their browser, microphone, virtual desktop infrastructure, and third-party identity provider statuses are verified. Additionally, agents using Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect run the Amazon Connect Endpoint Test Utility to verify their connection.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To set up the Voice Status utility:	
Customize Application AND View Setup and Configuration

To use the Voice Status utility:	
Contact Center Agent permission set OR Contact Center Admin permission set

Add the Voice Status utility to console apps so itâ€™s available to agents.
From Setup in Lightning Experience, enter App in the Quick Find box, and then select App Manager.
Click the dropdown next to the console app that you want to add Voice Status to, and then click Edit.
Under Utility Bar, click Add.
Click Voice Status.
Click Save.
Click Done.

Alternatively, to add Voice Status to Voice extensions, use Lightning App Builder to drag the Voice Status standard component to the Lightning pages used as extensions, and then click Save.
